00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:43,434
Just... You can't keep
doing this all the time.

490
00:36:43,520 --> 00:36:46,876
I can't help it. I love you.

491
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:51,078
Forrest...
You don't know what love is.

492
00:36:57,480 --> 00:37:00,278
You remember that time
we prayed, Forrest?

493
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:06,834
We prayed for God to turn me
into a bird so I could fly far away?

494
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:10,116
Yes, I do.

495
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:14,794
You think I could fly
off this bridge?

496
00:37:21,680 --> 00:37:24,672
What do you mean, Jenny?

497
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,952
Nothing.

498
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:34,356
I gotta get out of here.

499
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:39,351
- Wait, Jenny.
- Forrest, you stay away from me, OK?

500
00:37:39,440 --> 00:37:41,590
You stay away from me, please.

501
00:37:41,680 --> 00:37:44,274
- Can I have a ride?
- (Man) Where are you going?

502
00:37:44,360 --> 00:37:46,749
- I don't care.
- Get in the truck.

503
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,831
So bye-bye, Jenny.

504
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:52,919
They sending me to Vietnam.

505
00:37:55,120 --> 00:37:57,270
It's this whole other country.

506
00:37:59,880 --> 00:38:01,836
Just hang on a minute.

507
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:05,913
Listen, you promise me something, OK?

508
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,958
If you're ever in trouble,
don't be brave. Just run.

509
00:38:09,040 --> 00:38:11,759
OK? Just run away.

510
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:13,193
OK.

511
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:20,071
Jenny.

512
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:23,918
I'll write you all the time.

513
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:33,876
'And just like that,

514
00:38:33,960 --> 00:38:35,712
'she was gone.'

515
00:38:50,720 --> 00:38:53,996
You come back safe to me.
Do you hear?

516
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:14,233
# Some folks are born

517
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:16,515
# Made to wave the flag

518
00:39:16,600 --> 00:39:18,795
# Ooh, they're red, white, and blue

519
00:39:19,880 --> 00:39:23,236
# And when the band plays
"Hail to the chief"

520
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:26,676
# Ooh, they'll point
the cannon at you, Lord

521
00:39:26,760 --> 00:39:30,309
# It ain't me, it ain't me

522
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,960
# I ain't no senator's son, son

523
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,109
# It ain't me... #

524
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:39,398
'Now, they told us that Vietnam
was going to be very different

525
00:39:39,480 --> 00:39:41,550
'from the United States of America.

526
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:47,351
'Except for all the beer cans
and barbecues, it was.'

527
00:39:56,600 --> 00:39:59,592
Hey, I'll bet there's shrimp
all in these waters.

528
00:39:59,680 --> 00:40:02,478
They tell me these Vietnams
is good shrimp.

529
00:40:02,560 --> 00:40:06,075
After we win this war
and we take over everything,

530
00:40:06,160 --> 00:40:09,596
we can get American shrimpers out
here and shrimp these waters.

531
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:11,830
Just shrimp all the time, man.

532
00:40:14,080 --> 00:40:17,470
- You must be my FNGs.
- (Both) Morning, sir!

533
00:40:17,560 --> 00:40:20,313
Oh, get your hands down.
Do not salute me.

534
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:22,834
There are goddamn snipers
all around this area

535
00:40:22,920 --> 00:40:24,911
who'd love to grease an officer.

536
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:28,037
I'm Lieutenant Dan Taylor.
Welcome to Fort Platoon.

537
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:31,834
What's wrong with your lip?

538
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:34,115
I was born with big gums, sir.

539
00:40:34,200 --> 00:40:38,432
Well, you better tuck that in.
Gonna get that caught on a trip wire.

540
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:41,397
Where are you boys from in the world?

541
00:40:41,480 --> 00:40:43,198
(Both) Alabama, sir!

542
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,236
You twins?

543
00:40:47,320 --> 00:40:49,880
No. We are not relations, sir.

544
00:40:51,920 --> 00:40:54,434
Look, it's pretty basic here.

545
00:40:55,720 --> 00:40:59,429
You stick with me and learn from the
guys who've been in country a while,

546
00:40:59,520 --> 00:41:01,272
you'll be all right.

547
00:41:01,360 --> 00:41:03,351
There is one item of GI gear

548
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:06,193
that can be the difference
between life and death...

549
00:41:06,280 --> 00:41:07,679
socks.

550
00:41:07,760 --> 00:41:11,389
Cushioned sole, OD Green.
Try and keep your feet dry.

551
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:15,109
When we're out humpin',
change your socks whenever we stop.

552
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:18,510
The Mekong will eat
a grunt's feet right off his legs.

553
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:22,559
Sergeant Sims. God damn it, where's
that sling rope I told you to order?

554
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:24,073
I put in the requisitions.

555
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:26,355
Well, you call
those sons of bitches...

556
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:28,317
'Lieutenant Dan sure knew his stuff.

557
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:31,198
'l felt real lucky
he was my lieutenant.

558
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:34,875
'He was from a long,
great military tradition.

559
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:38,839
'Somebody in his family
had fought and died

560
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,433
'in every...

561
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:41,589
'single...

562
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:43,671
'American war.'

563
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:46,797
God damn it, kick some ass.
Get on it!

564
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:50,589
'l guess you could say
he had a lot to live up to.'

565
00:41:51,680 --> 00:41:56,390
So, you boys from Arkansas, huh?
Well...l been through there.

566
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:59,040
Little Rock's a fine town.

567
00:41:59,120 --> 00:42:02,157
Now, shake down your gear.
See the platoon sergeant.

568
00:42:02,240 --> 00:42:04,800
Draw what you need for the field.

569
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:09,032
If you boys are hungry, we got
steaks burning right over here.

570
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:11,714
Two standing orders in this platoon.

571
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:14,439
One, take good care of your feet.

572
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:17,830
Two, try not to do anything stupid,

573
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:19,911
Iike getting yourself killed.

574
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:24,676
# ..this is the worse trip
I've ever been on #

575
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:26,716
I sure hope I don't let him down.

576
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:41,233
'l got to see
a lot of the countryside.

577
00:42:41,320 --> 00:42:43,754
'We would take
these real long walks.'

578
00:42:45,760 --> 00:42:48,672
# There must be
some kinda way outta here

579
00:42:49,760 --> 00:42:51,796
# Said the joker to the thief... #

580
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:55,111
'And we were always lookin'
for this guy named Charlie.'

581
00:42:55,200 --> 00:43:00,672
# There's too much confusion,
I can't get no relief... #

582
00:43:03,120 --> 00:43:05,076
- Hold it up!
- Hold up, boys!

583
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:09,950
'lt wasn't always fun.'

584
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:14,272
'Lieutenant Dan was always getting
these funny feelings, about a rock

585
00:43:14,360 --> 00:43:16,510
'or a trail, or the road,

586
00:43:16,600 --> 00:43:19,160
'so he'd tell us
to get down, shut up.'

587
00:43:19,240 --> 00:43:21,470
Get down! Shut up!

588
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:24,351
'So we did.

589
00:43:40,400 --> 00:43:42,675
'Now, I don't know
much about anything,

590
00:43:42,760 --> 00:43:46,275
'but I think some of America's
best young men served in this war.

591
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:48,669
'There was Dallas from Phoenix...

592
00:43:49,760 --> 00:43:52,638
'Cleveland, he was from Detroit.

593
00:43:52,720 --> 00:43:55,837
Hey, Tex. Hey, Tex.

594
00:43:55,920 --> 00:43:57,433
What the hell's going on?

595
00:43:57,520 --> 00:43:59,590
'And Tex was...

596
00:43:59,680 --> 00:44:02,672
'Well, I don't remember
where Tex come from.'

597
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,432
(Dan) Ah, nothin'.

598
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:09,391
Fourth platoon, on your feet.

599
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:13,758
Y'all got 10 clicks
to go to that river. Move out.

600
00:44:13,840 --> 00:44:16,115
(Platoon) One, two, hup!

601
00:44:17,480 --> 00:44:20,199
(Dan) Step it up!
Look alive out there.

602
00:44:20,280 --> 00:44:23,795
'The good thing about Vietnam
is there was always someplace to go.'

603
00:44:23,880 --> 00:44:25,279
Fire in the hole!

604
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:31,069
Gump, check out that hole.

605
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:33,958
'And there was always
something to do.'

606
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:36,998
- Mount 'em up!
- Spread out! Cover his back!

607
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:47,590
'One day, it started raining,
and it didn't quit for four months.

608
00:44:47,680 --> 00:44:50,752
'We'd been through every
kind of rain there is.

609
00:44:50,840 --> 00:44:53,559
'Little bitty stinging rain

610
00:44:54,640 --> 00:44:57,359
'and big old fat rain,

611
00:44:57,440 --> 00:45:00,079
'rain that flew in sideways,

612
00:45:00,160 --> 00:45:05,109
'and sometimes rain even seemed to
come straight up from underneath.

613
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:08,476
'Shoot, it even rained at night.'

614
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:11,358
- Hey, Forrest.
- Hey, Bubba.

615
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:15,035
I'm going to lean up against you.
You lean back against me.

616
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:19,193
This way we don't have to sleep
with our heads in the mud.

617
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:21,714
You know why
we're a good partnership, Forrest?

618
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:26,749
Cos we be watching out for one
another, like brothers and stuff.

619
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:32,069
Hey, Forrest,
something I been thinking about.

620
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:34,993
I got a very important question
to ask you.

621
00:45:36,760 --> 00:45:40,355
How would you like to go
into the shrimping business with me?

622
00:45:41,960 --> 00:45:44,952
- OK.
- Man, I tell you what.

623
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:47,235
I got it all figured out, too.

624
00:45:47,320 --> 00:45:50,118
So many pounds of shrimp
will pay off the boat.

625
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:53,351
So many pounds for gas.
We'll live right on the boat.

626
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:55,670
We ain't got to pay no rent.

627
00:45:55,760 --> 00:45:59,469
We can just work it together, split
everything right down the middle.

628
00:45:59,560 --> 00:46:04,554
Man, I'm telling you, 50-50. And hey,
Forrest, all the shrimp you can eat.

629
00:46:06,120 --> 00:46:08,509
That's a fine idea.

630
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:11,398
'Bubba did have a fine idea.

631
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:17,837
'l even wrote Jenny
and told her all about it.

632
00:46:17,920 --> 00:46:21,469
'l sent her letters.
Not every day, but almost.

633
00:46:21,560 --> 00:46:26,076
'l told her what I was doing
and asked her what she was doing,

634
00:46:26,160 --> 00:46:29,232
'and told her
how I thought about her always.

635
00:46:30,480 --> 00:46:34,268
'And how I was looking forward
to getting a letter from her

636
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:37,113
'just as soon as she had the time.

637
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:39,953
'l'd always let her know
that I was OK.

638
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:46,718
'Then I'd sign each letter
"Love, Forrest Gump."'

639
00:46:56,720 --> 00:47:00,474
# There's somethin'
happenin' here... #

640
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:03,916
'This one day,
we was out walking like always,

641
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:07,356
'and then, just like that,

642
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:09,670
'somebody turned off the rain,

643
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:11,193
'and the sun come out.'

644
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:13,874
# I got to beware... #

645
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:17,953
(Dan) Ambush! Take cover!

646
00:47:26,080 --> 00:47:28,719
Get that pig up here, God damn it!

647
00:47:28,800 --> 00:47:30,950
Forrest! You OK?

648
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:35,630
Strongarm, Strongarm!

649
00:47:37,680 --> 00:47:38,999
We got a man down!

650
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:42,356
Strongarm, this is Leg Lima 6! Over!

651
00:47:42,440 --> 00:47:47,116
Roger, Strongarm! We have incoming
from the treeline at point blue.

652
00:47:47,200 --> 00:47:50,636
Point blue! AKs and rockets!
We're getting it hard!

653
00:47:50,720 --> 00:47:52,119
Misfire! Misfire!

654
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,033
God damn it!

655
00:47:55,920 --> 00:48:00,277
Get that pig unfucked
and get it in the treeline!

656
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:05,152
Jesus! My unit is down hard
and hurting!

657
00:48:05,240 --> 00:48:07,993
Pullin' back to the blue line.
Leg Lima 6 out!

658
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:10,831
Pull back! Pull back!

659
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:14,595
- Forrest! Run, Forrest!
- Pull back!

660
00:48:14,680 --> 00:48:17,513
Come on! Run, man! Run!

661
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:19,113
(Dan) Pull back, Gump!

662
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:23,675
Run, God damn it! Run!

663
00:48:43,760 --> 00:48:45,830
(Soldier) Medic!

664
00:48:45,920 --> 00:48:48,354
Can I get a medic?

665
00:48:48,440 --> 00:48:52,399
'l ran and ran,
just like Jenny told me to.

666
00:48:54,920 --> 00:48:56,990
'l ran so far and so fast

667
00:48:57,080 --> 00:49:00,959
'that pretty soon I was all
by myself, which was a bad thing.'

668
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:02,837
Bubba.

669
00:49:04,640 --> 00:49:09,031
'Bubba was my best good friend.
I had to make sure he was OK.'

670
00:49:17,720 --> 00:49:20,109
(Man) Where the hell are you?

671
00:49:20,200 --> 00:49:22,031
Bubba!

672
00:49:22,120 --> 00:49:24,918
'And on my way back to find Bubba,

673
00:49:25,000 --> 00:49:27,753
'well, there was this boy
laying on the ground.'

674
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:28,875
Tex.

675
00:49:30,760 --> 00:49:31,749
OK.

676
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:35,958
'l couldn't just let him lay there
all alone, scared the way he was,

677
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:39,589
'so I grabbed him up
and run him out of there.

678
00:49:54,080 --> 00:49:56,833
'Every time I went back
looking for Bubba,

679
00:49:56,920 --> 00:50:01,152
'somebody else was saying,
"Help me, Forrest, help me!"'

680
00:50:07,280 --> 00:50:09,510
OK. Here. Here.

681
00:50:11,760 --> 00:50:14,593
No sweat, man.
Lay back. You'll be OK.

682
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:21,031
'l started to get scared
that I might never find Bubba.'

683
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:26,752
I know my position is danger close!
We got Charlie all over this area.

684
00:50:26,840 --> 00:50:29,638
I got to have those fast movers
in here now. Over.

685
00:50:29,720 --> 00:50:31,950
Lieutenant Dan, Coleman's dead!

686
00:50:32,040 --> 00:50:36,352
I know he's dead! My whole
goddamn platoon is wiped out!

687
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:41,150
God damn it! What are you doing?
You leave me here!

688
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:44,630
Get away.
Just leave me here! Get out!

689
00:50:44,720 --> 00:50:48,235
Aah! God, I said
leave me here, God damn it!

690
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:50,709
'Leg Lima six, this is Strongarm.

691
00:50:50,800 --> 00:50:53,792
'Be advised
your fast movers are inbound. Over.'

692
00:50:53,880 --> 00:50:56,838
'Then it felt like something
just jumped up and bit me.'

693
00:50:56,920 --> 00:50:59,798
Aah! Something bit me!

694
00:51:03,880 --> 00:51:06,314
(Dan screams)

695
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:09,631
You son of a bitch! Aah!

696
00:51:09,720 --> 00:51:15,272
I can't leave the platoon.
I told you to leave me there, Gump!

697
00:51:15,360 --> 00:51:19,478
Forget about me. Get yourself out!
Did you hear what I said?

698
00:51:19,560 --> 00:51:23,872
Gump, damn it, put me down!
Get your ass out of here!

699
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:29,477
I didn't ask you to pull me out
of there, God damn you!

700
00:51:29,560 --> 00:51:32,757
- Where do you think you're going?
- To get Bubba.

701
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:36,594
I got an air strike inbound now.
They're going to nape the whole area.

702
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:39,240
Stay here, God damn it!
That's an order!

703
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:41,709
I gotta find Bubba!

704
00:51:56,400 --> 00:51:58,311
(Bubba) Forrest.

705
00:52:05,040 --> 00:52:06,519
Bubba.

706
00:52:06,600 --> 00:52:09,831
I'm OK, Forrest. I'm OK.

707
00:52:17,960 --> 00:52:21,509
- Oh, Bubba, no.
- I'm gonna be all right.

708
00:52:24,240 --> 00:52:26,390
(Vietnamese soldiers approaching)

709
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:32,349
Come on. Come on. Come on.

710
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:38,680
Ugh. I'm OK, Forrest.

711
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:41,399
(Aeroplanes overhead)

712
00:52:41,480 --> 00:52:43,357
I'm OK. I'm fine.

713
00:53:18,480 --> 00:53:21,517
(Dan) Top smoke. Get it out there.

714
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:24,592
'lf I'd have known this
was going to be the last time

715
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:26,636
'me and Bubba was gonna talk,

716
00:53:26,720 --> 00:53:29,029
'l'd of thought
of something better to say.'

717
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:32,999
- Hey, Bubba.
- Hey, Forrest.

718
00:53:34,880 --> 00:53:36,233
Forrest...

719
00:53:36,320 --> 00:53:38,595
why did this happen?

720
00:53:39,840 --> 00:53:41,592
You got shot.

721
00:53:42,680 --> 00:53:46,355
'Then Bubba said something
I won't ever forget.'

722
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:49,829
I want to go home.

723
00:53:50,880 --> 00:53:53,269
'Bubba was my best good friend.

724
00:53:53,360 --> 00:53:57,876
'And even I know that ain't something
you can find just around the corner.

725
00:53:57,960 --> 00:54:01,077
'Bubba was going to be
a shrimping boat captain,

726
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:06,188
'but instead, he died right
there by that river in Vietnam.'

727
00:54:09,360 --> 00:54:11,316
That's all I have to say about that.

728
00:54:15,080 --> 00:54:17,230
It was a bullet, wasn't it?

729
00:54:19,040 --> 00:54:22,112
- A bullet?
- That jumped up and bit you.

730
00:54:24,240 --> 00:54:26,196
Oh. Yes, sir.

731
00:54:26,280 --> 00:54:28,510
Bit me directly in the but-tocks.

