01:31:47,840 --> 01:31:49,432
Ha ha! Ha ha!

1221
01:31:49,520 --> 01:31:53,354
You'll never sink...this...boat!

1222
01:31:53,440 --> 01:31:55,237
Ha ha ha ha!

1223
01:31:55,320 --> 01:31:57,276
Hurricane Carmen
came through yesterday,

1224
01:31:57,360 --> 01:31:59,669
destroying nearly everything
in its path.

1225
01:31:59,760 --> 01:32:02,320
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

1226
01:32:02,400 --> 01:32:04,834
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

1227
01:32:04,920 --> 01:32:09,914
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

1228
01:32:10,000 --> 01:32:11,956
'This reporter has learned,

1229
01:32:12,040 --> 01:32:15,271
'in fact, only one shrimping boat
survived the storm.'

1230
01:32:15,360 --> 01:32:17,715
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1231
01:32:17,800 --> 01:32:20,758
'After that, shrimping was easy.'

1232
01:32:20,840 --> 01:32:23,479
(Gospel choir)
# There will be great bounty

1233
01:32:23,560 --> 01:32:26,233
# Oh, my God... #

1234
01:32:26,320 --> 01:32:30,359
Since people still needed shrimps
for shrimp cocktails and barbecues,

1235
01:32:30,440 --> 01:32:33,432
and we were the only
boat left standing,

1236
01:32:33,520 --> 01:32:35,875
Bubba-Gump shrimp's what they got.

1237
01:32:35,960 --> 01:32:38,793
We got a whole bunch of boats.

1238
01:32:38,880 --> 01:32:41,394
Twelve Jennys, big old warehouse.

1239
01:32:41,480 --> 01:32:44,950
We even have hats
that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

1240
01:32:45,040 --> 01:32:47,838
Bubba-Gump Shrimp.
It's a household name.

1241
01:32:47,920 --> 01:32:49,319
Hold on there, boy.

1242
01:32:49,400 --> 01:32:53,916
Are you telling me you're the owner
of the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

1243
01:32:54,000 --> 01:32:56,798
Yes, sir. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1244
01:32:58,400 --> 01:33:01,915
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time, but that tops them all.

1245
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:04,309
(Laughs)

1246
01:33:04,400 --> 01:33:07,756
We were sitting next
to a millionaire!

1247
01:33:10,600 --> 01:33:15,515
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

1248
01:33:15,600 --> 01:33:20,515
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

1249
01:33:20,600 --> 01:33:24,434
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1250
01:33:24,520 --> 01:33:26,750
Yes, I would.

1251
01:33:30,880 --> 01:33:32,632
That's him right there.

1252
01:33:34,640 --> 01:33:37,438
Let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan.

1253
01:33:37,520 --> 01:33:39,158
Forrest...

1254
01:33:44,480 --> 01:33:48,075
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

1255
01:34:12,600 --> 01:34:14,795
'He never actually said so,

1256
01:34:14,880 --> 01:34:18,634
'but I think
he made his peace with God.'

1257
01:34:24,120 --> 01:34:26,076
(Gunshots)

1258
01:34:26,160 --> 01:34:27,912
'For the second time in 17 days,

1259
01:34:28,000 --> 01:34:31,436
'President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.'

1260
01:34:31,520 --> 01:34:34,512
(Radio) 'Base to Jenny 1 .
Base to Jenny 1 .'

1261
01:34:34,600 --> 01:34:35,953
Jenny 1 . Go, Margo.

1262
01:34:36,040 --> 01:34:37,871
'Forrest has a phone call.'

1263
01:34:37,960 --> 01:34:40,349
Well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

1264
01:34:40,440 --> 01:34:42,271
He is indisposed at the moment.

1265
01:34:42,360 --> 01:34:44,510
'His mama's sick.'

1266
01:35:02,760 --> 01:35:05,797
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

1267
01:35:07,760 --> 01:35:09,830
Hi, Forrest.

1268
01:35:09,920 --> 01:35:11,911
(Doctor) I'll see you tomorrow.

1269
01:35:12,000 --> 01:35:13,752
All right.

1270
01:35:19,560 --> 01:35:23,075
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1271
01:35:33,440 --> 01:35:35,192
What's the matter, Mama?

1272
01:35:36,280 --> 01:35:38,271
I'm dying, Forrest.

1273
01:35:40,360 --> 01:35:43,158
Come on in, sit down over here.

1274
01:35:56,200 --> 01:35:58,270
Why are you dying, Mama?

1275
01:35:59,320 --> 01:36:01,276
It's my time.

1276
01:36:01,360 --> 01:36:03,351
It's just my time.

1277
01:36:03,440 --> 01:36:05,749
Oh, now...

1278
01:36:06,840 --> 01:36:09,991
Don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

1279
01:36:10,080 --> 01:36:12,230
Death is just a part of life.

1280
01:36:12,320 --> 01:36:15,039
Something we're all destined to do.

1281
01:36:17,280 --> 01:36:21,831
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

1282
01:36:21,920 --> 01:36:24,388
I did the best I could.

1283
01:36:24,480 --> 01:36:26,436
You did good, Mama.

1284
01:36:26,520 --> 01:36:31,594
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1285
01:36:32,920 --> 01:36:36,469
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1286
01:36:39,760 --> 01:36:42,274
What's my destiny, Mama?

1287
01:36:43,800 --> 01:36:46,837
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1288
01:36:47,920 --> 01:36:50,753
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1289
01:36:50,840 --> 01:36:53,593
You never know
what you're going to get.

1290
01:36:53,680 --> 01:36:57,753
'Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.'

1291
01:36:57,840 --> 01:36:59,796
I will miss you, Forrest.

1292
01:37:01,400 --> 01:37:03,675
'She had got the cancer

1293
01:37:03,760 --> 01:37:05,876
'and died on a Tuesday.

1294
01:37:06,960 --> 01:37:10,111
'l bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.'

1295
01:37:13,080 --> 01:37:16,072
And that's all I have
to say about that.

1296
01:37:22,280 --> 01:37:25,238
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1297
01:37:25,320 --> 01:37:28,392
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1298
01:37:31,160 --> 01:37:35,438
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1299
01:37:35,520 --> 01:37:38,353
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1300
01:37:38,440 --> 01:37:42,149
and a college graduate, the city
fathers of Greenbow, Alabama,

1301
01:37:42,240 --> 01:37:44,879
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1302
01:37:46,120 --> 01:37:49,476
'So I never went back
to work for Lieutenant Dan,

1303
01:37:49,560 --> 01:37:52,233
'though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1304
01:37:52,320 --> 01:37:55,153
'He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1305
01:37:55,240 --> 01:37:57,629
So then I got a call from him

1306
01:37:57,720 --> 01:38:00,154
saying we don't have to worry
about money no more,

1307
01:38:00,240 --> 01:38:04,438
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1308
01:38:04,520 --> 01:38:06,238
# I've got a new hope... #

1309
01:38:06,320 --> 01:38:10,279
'Now Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1310
01:38:10,360 --> 01:38:13,591
'and the rest
is just for showing off.

1311
01:38:13,680 --> 01:38:18,993
'So I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare Gospel Church.

1312
01:38:19,720 --> 01:38:24,555
'And I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1313
01:38:26,000 --> 01:38:31,597
'And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,

1314
01:38:31,680 --> 01:38:34,956
'l gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.'

1315
01:38:37,600 --> 01:38:39,192
You know what?

1316
01:38:40,400 --> 01:38:43,551
'She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.'

1317
01:38:43,640 --> 01:38:45,596
That smells wonderful.

1318
01:38:45,680 --> 01:38:50,800
'And cos I was a gozillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1319
01:38:50,880 --> 01:38:52,836
'l cut that grass for free.

1320
01:38:55,520 --> 01:38:58,910
'But at night-time
when there was nothing to do

1321
01:38:59,000 --> 01:39:01,468
'and the house was all empty,

1322
01:39:01,560 --> 01:39:04,120
'l'd always think of Jenny.'

1323
01:40:05,160 --> 01:40:08,869
'And then...she was there.'

1324
01:40:40,160 --> 01:40:43,755
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1325
01:40:54,080 --> 01:40:57,038
'Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1326
01:40:58,280 --> 01:41:01,750
'Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1327
01:41:01,840 --> 01:41:05,628
'or maybe it was because she was
so tired cos she went to bed

1328
01:41:05,720 --> 01:41:10,157
'and slept and slept
like she hadn't slept in years.

1329
01:41:10,840 --> 01:41:12,956
'lt was wonderful having her home.

1330
01:41:14,200 --> 01:41:19,320
'Every day we'd take a walk, and I'd
jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1331
01:41:19,400 --> 01:41:22,153
'and she'd listen about
ping ponging and shrimping

1332
01:41:22,240 --> 01:41:24,310
'and Mama making a trip up to heaven.

1333
01:41:24,400 --> 01:41:26,152
'l did all the talking.

1334
01:41:26,240 --> 01:41:29,391
'Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.'

1335
01:42:07,360 --> 01:42:10,113
How could you do this?

1336
01:42:45,720 --> 01:42:50,077
'Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.

1337
01:42:51,360 --> 01:42:55,797
'l never really knew
why she came back, but I didn't care.

1338
01:42:55,880 --> 01:43:00,431
'lt was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.

1339
01:43:01,920 --> 01:43:06,835
'Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,

1340
01:43:07,920 --> 01:43:09,911
'and she gave me the best gift

1341
01:43:10,000 --> 01:43:12,275
'anyone could ever get
in the wide world.'

1342
01:43:12,360 --> 01:43:13,952
They're just for running.

1343
01:43:17,880 --> 01:43:20,917
'And she even showed me
how to dance.'

1344
01:43:22,720 --> 01:43:25,109
# I miss the whole family once again

1345
01:43:25,200 --> 01:43:27,634
# And I think it's a sin

1346
01:43:27,720 --> 01:43:30,314
# Sweet home Alabama... #

1347
01:43:30,400 --> 01:43:34,313
'Well, we was like family,
Jenny and me...

1348
01:43:37,080 --> 01:43:40,277
'and it was the happiest time
in my life.'

1349
01:44:03,560 --> 01:44:06,074
- You done watching it?
- Mm-hmm.

1350
01:44:06,160 --> 01:44:08,116
I'm going to bed.

1351
01:44:17,880 --> 01:44:20,110
Will you marry me?

1352
01:44:24,120 --> 01:44:27,396
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1353
01:44:29,880 --> 01:44:31,757
You would, Forrest.

1354
01:44:33,640 --> 01:44:35,790
But you won't marry me.

1355
01:44:37,640 --> 01:44:40,393
You don't want to marry me.

1356
01:44:43,320 --> 01:44:45,675
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1357
01:44:50,640 --> 01:44:52,995
I'm not a smart man,

1358
01:44:54,440 --> 01:44:56,590
but I know what love is.

1359
01:45:32,520 --> 01:45:33,919
Jenny...

1360
01:45:35,400 --> 01:45:38,233
Forrest, I do love you.

1361
01:46:28,680 --> 01:46:31,399
Where are you running off to?

1362
01:46:31,480 --> 01:46:33,436
I'm not running.

1363
01:48:00,280 --> 01:48:03,113
'That day, for no particular reason,

1364
01:48:03,200 --> 01:48:05,714
'l decided to go for a little run.

1365
01:48:05,800 --> 01:48:09,713
'So I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there

1366
01:48:09,800 --> 01:48:12,360
'l thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.

1367
01:48:12,440 --> 01:48:15,432
(TV) 'President Carter,
suffering from heat exhaustion...'

1368
01:48:15,520 --> 01:48:16,953
'And when I got there,

1369
01:48:17,040 --> 01:48:21,033
'l thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.

1370
01:48:21,120 --> 01:48:23,509
'Now, thinking since I'd run
this far,

1371
01:48:23,600 --> 01:48:27,275
'maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.

1372
01:48:27,360 --> 01:48:30,875
'And that's what I did.
I ran clear across Alabama.'

1373
01:48:31,600 --> 01:48:35,149
No particular reason.
I just kept on going.

1374
01:48:35,240 --> 01:48:37,231
I ran clear to the ocean.

1375
01:48:42,520 --> 01:48:46,479
'And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1376
01:48:46,560 --> 01:48:49,632
'might as well turn around,
just keep on going.

1377
01:48:53,000 --> 01:48:57,232
'And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far...

1378
01:48:59,240 --> 01:49:02,676
'l might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.

1379
01:49:03,760 --> 01:49:08,038
'When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.'

1380
01:49:08,120 --> 01:49:13,672
When I had to go...
you know... I went.

1381
01:49:13,760 --> 01:49:16,957
And so, you just ran.

1382
01:49:18,600 --> 01:49:19,999
Yeah.

1383
01:49:20,080 --> 01:49:23,993
# Lookin' out at the road
rushin' under my wheels

1384
01:49:27,040 --> 01:49:29,395
# Lookin' back at the years gone by

1385
01:49:29,480 --> 01:49:31,914
# Like so many sown fields

1386
01:49:33,560 --> 01:49:36,313
# ln '65, I was 17

1387
01:49:36,400 --> 01:49:38,709
# And runnin' up on one

1388
01:49:40,200 --> 01:49:42,589
# I don't know where I'm runnin' now

1389
01:49:42,680 --> 01:49:45,638
# I'm just runnin' on

1390
01:49:45,720 --> 01:49:47,392
# Runnin' on

1391
01:49:47,480 --> 01:49:49,311
# Runnin' on empty

1392
01:49:49,400 --> 01:49:50,719
# Runnin' on

1393
01:49:50,800 --> 01:49:52,756
# Runnin' blind... #

1394
01:49:53,840 --> 01:49:59,233
'l'd think a lot, about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.

1395
01:49:59,320 --> 01:50:03,393
'But most of all,
I thought about Jenny.

1396
01:50:03,480 --> 01:50:05,789
'l thought about her a lot.'

1397
01:50:06,880 --> 01:50:09,838
'For more than two years,
a man named Forrest Gump,

1398
01:50:09,920 --> 01:50:13,071
'a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,

1399
01:50:13,160 --> 01:50:15,310
'has been running across America.

1400
01:50:15,400 --> 01:50:17,595
'Charles Cooper
brings you this report.'

1401
01:50:17,680 --> 01:50:20,592
'For the fourth time
on his journey across America,

1402
01:50:20,680 --> 01:50:22,591
'Forrest Gump, the gardener,

1403
01:50:22,680 --> 01:50:26,593
'is about to cross
the Mississippi River again today.'

1404
01:50:26,680 --> 01:50:28,750
I'll be damned. Forrest?

1405
01:50:28,840 --> 01:50:32,958
- Are you doing this for world peace?
- Is it for the homeless?

1406
01:50:33,040 --> 01:50:36,396
- Are you running for women's rights?
- The environment?

1407
01:50:36,480 --> 01:50:39,552
'They couldn't believe that somebody
would do all that running

1408
01:50:39,640 --> 01:50:41,198
'for no particular reason.'

1409
01:50:41,280 --> 01:50:45,398
- Why are you doing this?
- I just felt like running.

1410
01:50:45,480 --> 01:50:47,038
I just felt like runnin'.

1411
01:50:48,200 --> 01:50:51,510
That's you.
I can't believe it's really you.

1412
01:50:51,600 --> 01:50:56,879
Now, for some reason, what I was
doing seemed to make sense to people.

1413
01:50:56,960 --> 01:50:59,269
It was like an alarm
went off in my head.

1414
01:50:59,360 --> 01:51:02,511
I said, "Here's a guy
that's got his act together.

1415
01:51:02,600 --> 01:51:06,673
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr Gump.

1416
01:51:06,760 --> 01:51:08,910
'So I got company.

1417
01:51:10,440 --> 01:51:13,716
'And after that, I got more company.

1418
01:51:13,800 --> 01:51:16,837
'And then,
even more people joined in.'

1419
01:51:18,320 --> 01:51:21,312
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1420
01:51:23,080 --> 01:51:26,595
Now, I don't know anything
about that,

1421
01:51:26,680 --> 01:51:31,037
but some of those people asked me
if I could help them out.

1422
01:51:31,120 --> 01:51:35,432
I was wondering if you might help me.
I'm in the bumper sticker business.

1423
01:51:35,520 --> 01:51:38,876
I need a good slogan, and since
you've been so inspirational,

1424
01:51:38,960 --> 01:51:41,394
I thought you might
be able to help me...

1425
01:51:41,480 --> 01:51:45,473
Whoa, man! You just ran
through a big pile of dog shit!

1426
01:51:46,680 --> 01:51:49,592
- It happens.
- What? Shit?

1427
01:51:50,640 --> 01:51:52,392
Sometimes.

1428
01:51:54,160 --> 01:51:57,516
'And some years later, I heard
that that fella did come up

1429
01:51:57,600 --> 01:52:01,832
'with a bumper sticker slogan
and made a lot of money off of it.

1430
01:52:01,920 --> 01:52:04,115
'Another time, I was running along.

1431
01:52:04,200 --> 01:52:07,670
'Somebody who'd lost all his money
in the t-shirt business,

1432
01:52:07,760 --> 01:52:10,115
'he wanted to put my face
on a t-shirt,

1433
01:52:10,200 --> 01:52:13,954
'but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.'

1434
01:52:14,040 --> 01:52:17,430
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that colour anyway.

1435
01:52:17,520 --> 01:52:19,238
(Horn honks)

1436
01:52:21,400 --> 01:52:23,152
Have a nice day.

1437
01:52:24,880 --> 01:52:26,791
'Some years later, I found out

1438
01:52:26,880 --> 01:52:29,952
'that that man did come up
with an idea for a t-shirt.

1439
01:52:30,040 --> 01:52:32,076
'He made a lot of money off of it.'

1440
01:52:34,440 --> 01:52:39,036
'Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.

1441
01:52:40,120 --> 01:52:43,829
'My mama always said,
"You got to put the past behind you

1442
01:52:43,920 --> 01:52:45,876
"'before you can move on."

1443
01:52:45,960 --> 01:52:49,714
'And I think
that's what my running was all about.

1444
01:52:51,120 --> 01:52:53,554
'l had run for three years...

1445
01:52:53,640 --> 01:52:57,679
'two months, 14 days, and 16 hours.'

1446
01:53:12,240 --> 01:53:14,435
Quiet. He's going to say something.

1447
01:53:25,640 --> 01:53:27,756
I'm pretty tired.

1448
01:53:30,080 --> 01:53:32,036
Think I'll go home now.

1449
01:53:49,600 --> 01:53:51,795
Now what are we supposed to do?

1450
01:53:52,880 --> 01:53:57,635
'And just like that,
my runnin' days was over.

1451
01:53:57,720 --> 01:53:59,870
'So I went home to Alabama.'

1452
01:54:01,480 --> 01:54:03,391
(Reporter) 'Moments ago, at 2:25pm,

1453
01:54:03,480 --> 01:54:05,710
'as President Reagan
was leaving the...'

1454
01:54:05,800 --> 01:54:07,552
(Gunshots)

1455
01:54:07,640 --> 01:54:11,474
'..five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.

1456
01:54:11,560 --> 01:54:13,755
'The President was shot
in the chest...'

1457
01:54:13,840 --> 01:54:15,319
I picked up the mail.

1458
01:54:15,400 --> 01:54:20,110
And one day, out of the blue clear
sky, I got a letter from Jenny

1459
01:54:20,200 --> 01:54:24,398
wondering if I could
come down to Savannah and see her,

1460
01:54:24,480 --> 01:54:27,074
and that's what I'm doing here.

1461
01:54:27,160 --> 01:54:29,230
She saw me on TV, running.

1462
01:54:29,320 --> 01:54:33,552
I'm supposed to go on the number nine
bus to Richmond Street

1463
01:54:33,640 --> 01:54:40,239
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, apartment 4.

1464
01:54:40,320 --> 01:54:43,676
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1465
01:54:43,760 --> 01:54:48,470
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1466
01:54:50,120 --> 01:54:52,680
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1467
01:54:54,680 --> 01:54:56,432
It was nice talking to you.

1468
01:54:57,560 --> 01:54:58,595
(Horn honks)

1469
01:54:58,680 --> 01:55:00,989
I hope everything works out for you!

1470
01:55:08,320 --> 01:55:11,869
Hey! Forrest!

1471
01:55:11,960 --> 01:55:13,598
How you doin'?

1472
01:55:13,680 --> 01:55:16,478
- Come in! Come in!
- I got your letter.

1473
01:55:16,560 --> 01:55:22,317
- Oh, I was wondering about that.
- This your house?

1474
01:55:22,400 --> 01:55:25,119
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1475
01:55:25,200 --> 01:55:29,113
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1476
01:55:31,920 --> 01:55:33,592
Uh...

1477
01:55:35,480 --> 01:55:38,677
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1478
01:55:39,800 --> 01:55:43,839
I, uh, kept...kept a scrapbook of
...of your clippings and...

1479
01:55:44,560 --> 01:55:46,357
everything, there you are.

1480
01:55:48,200 --> 01:55:50,350
And this, I got you running.

1481
01:55:52,560 --> 01:55:56,599
I ran a long way. It's a long time.

1482
01:55:58,960 --> 01:56:00,313
There...

1483
01:56:06,640 --> 01:56:10,110
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this. Um...

1484
01:56:12,360 --> 01:56:14,032
I just...

1485
01:56:14,120 --> 01:56:18,636
I want to apologise for anything
that I ever did to you cos...

1486
01:56:18,720 --> 01:56:21,712
I was messed up...
for a long time, and...

1487
01:56:21,800 --> 01:56:23,074
(Knock on door)

1488
01:56:23,160 --> 01:56:25,071
- Yoo-hoo!
- Hey!

1489
01:56:25,160 --> 01:56:27,196
- Hi.
- Hey, you.

1490
01:56:27,280 --> 01:56:30,989
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1491
01:56:31,080 --> 01:56:34,390
(Jenny) Next week
my schedule changes, so I can...

1492
01:56:34,480 --> 01:56:36,675
No problem.
Got to go. I'm double-parked.

1493
01:56:36,760 --> 01:56:38,557
OK. Thanks.

1494
01:56:40,240 --> 01:56:43,949
This is my very good friend Mr Gump.
Can you say hi?

1495
01:56:44,040 --> 01:56:46,395
- Hello, Mr Gump.
- Hello.

1496
01:56:46,480 --> 01:56:50,359
- Can I go watch TV now?
- Yes. Just keep it low.

1497
01:56:52,480 --> 01:56:55,552
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1498
01:56:58,760 --> 01:57:01,513
His name's Forrest.

1499
01:57:01,600 --> 01:57:03,352
Like me!

1500
01:57:04,640 --> 01:57:06,995
I named him after his daddy.

1501
01:57:07,080 --> 01:57:09,753
He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1502
01:57:10,880 --> 01:57:12,916
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1503
01:57:27,080 --> 01:57:28,308
Hey...

1504
01:57:28,400 --> 01:57:31,836
Forrest, look at me.
Look at me, Forrest.

1505
01:57:34,480 --> 01:57:38,632
There's nothing you need to do.
You didn't do anything wrong.

1506
01:57:38,720 --> 01:57:40,073
OK?

1507
01:57:44,000 --> 01:57:45,752
Isn't he beautiful?

1508
01:57:46,960 --> 01:57:51,238
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1509
01:57:53,600 --> 01:57:55,272
But...

1510
01:57:57,480 --> 01:58:00,597
Is...is he s-smart? Like, can he...

1511
01:58:00,680 --> 01:58:05,071
He's very smart. He's one
of the smartest in his class.

1512
01:58:13,200 --> 01:58:15,873
Yeah, that's OK. Go talk to him.

1513
01:58:24,720 --> 01:58:27,553
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1514
01:58:49,920 --> 01:58:51,831
Forrest...

1515
01:58:52,920 --> 01:58:54,672
I'm sick.

1516
01:58:57,160 --> 01:58:59,754
What, do you have
a cough due to a cold?

1517
01:58:59,840 --> 01:59:05,472
I have some virus, and the doctors,
they don't know what it is,

1518
01:59:05,560 --> 01:59:08,120
and there isn't
anything they can do about it.

1519
01:59:12,680 --> 01:59:15,433
You could come home with me.

1520
01:59:16,600 --> 01:59:22,436
Jenny, you and...Little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1521
01:59:25,720 --> 01:59:28,757
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1522
01:59:30,920 --> 01:59:32,911
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1523
01:59:38,280 --> 01:59:39,235
OK.

1524
01:59:40,880 --> 01:59:42,836
(Man) Please take your seats.

1525
01:59:45,680 --> 01:59:48,592
Forrest? It's time to start.

1526
02:00:06,600 --> 02:00:07,953
Hi.

1527
02:00:09,040 --> 02:00:10,792
Your tie.

1528
02:00:22,240 --> 02:00:24,435
Lieutenant Dan.

1529
02:00:38,600 --> 02:00:40,192
Lieutenant Dan.

1530
02:00:41,200 --> 02:00:42,758
Hello, Forrest.

1531
02:00:43,920 --> 02:00:45,512
You got new legs.

1532
02:00:45,600 --> 02:00:47,158
New legs!

1533
02:00:47,240 --> 02:00:51,392
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1534
02:00:51,480 --> 02:00:55,632
Titanium alloy. It's what they use
on the space shuttle.

1535
02:00:59,080 --> 02:01:00,832
Magic legs.

1536
02:01:02,600 --> 02:01:06,957
