1537
02:01:09,280 --> 02:01:13,831
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1538
02:01:13,920 --> 02:01:18,391
Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.

1539
02:01:18,480 --> 02:01:21,278
Hi. It's nice to meet you finally.

1540
02:01:30,960 --> 02:01:34,873
Do you, Forrest,
take Jenny to be your wife?

1541
02:01:36,520 --> 02:01:40,513
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1542
02:01:42,080 --> 02:01:45,356
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1543
02:02:14,880 --> 02:02:16,996
- Hey.
- Hi.

1544
02:02:29,480 --> 02:02:31,232
Hey, Forrest...

1545
02:02:36,520 --> 02:02:38,476
Were you scared in Vietnam?

1546
02:02:39,800 --> 02:02:44,237
Yes. Well, l... I don't know.

1547
02:02:45,240 --> 02:02:50,519
'Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out...

1548
02:02:53,240 --> 02:02:55,117
'and then it was nice.'

1549
02:02:58,360 --> 02:03:02,672
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1550
02:03:02,760 --> 02:03:07,470
'There was always a million sparkles
on the water...

1551
02:03:09,040 --> 02:03:11,076
'like that mountain lake.

1552
02:03:11,160 --> 02:03:13,116
'lt was so clear, Jenny,

1553
02:03:13,200 --> 02:03:17,876
'it looked like there were two skies,
one on top of the other.'

1554
02:03:19,440 --> 02:03:22,671
And then in the desert,
when the sun comes up...

1555
02:03:25,240 --> 02:03:31,713
I couldn't tell where heaven stopped
and the earth began.

1556
02:03:33,440 --> 02:03:35,396
'lt's so beautiful.'

1557
02:03:39,400 --> 02:03:42,198
I wish I could've been there
with you.

1558
02:03:45,320 --> 02:03:47,231
You were.

1559
02:03:57,080 --> 02:03:58,718
I love you.

1560
02:04:02,560 --> 02:04:05,597
'You died on a Saturday morning.'

1561
02:04:07,360 --> 02:04:11,353
And I had you placed
here under our tree.

1562
02:04:15,600 --> 02:04:21,072
And I had that house of your father's
bulldozed to the ground.

1563
02:04:24,760 --> 02:04:31,677
Mama...always said
that dyin' was a part of life.

1564
02:04:34,800 --> 02:04:36,756
I sure wish it wasn't.

1565
02:04:39,760 --> 02:04:43,799
Little Forrest is...doing just fine.

1566
02:04:44,720 --> 02:04:46,597
"But..."

1567
02:04:46,680 --> 02:04:49,148
About to start school again soon,

1568
02:04:50,120 --> 02:04:54,272
and I make his breakfast,
lunch, and dinner every day.

1569
02:04:56,040 --> 02:05:01,990
I make sure he...combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1570
02:05:04,520 --> 02:05:10,390
Teaching him how to play ping pong.
He's really good.

1571
02:05:10,480 --> 02:05:13,677
Uh, Forrest, you go. Uhh!

1572
02:05:17,000 --> 02:05:19,116
'We fish a lot.'

1573
02:05:22,320 --> 02:05:25,995
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1574
02:05:28,280 --> 02:05:30,350
You'd be so proud of him.

1575
02:05:31,960 --> 02:05:33,359
I am.

1576
02:05:34,440 --> 02:05:37,238
He, uh, wrote you a...a letter.

1577
02:05:38,320 --> 02:05:40,880
And he says I can't read it.

1578
02:05:40,960 --> 02:05:44,475
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1579
02:06:00,120 --> 02:06:01,872
Jenny...

1580
02:06:06,680 --> 02:06:12,516
I don't know if Mama was right
or if it...it's Lieutenant Dan.

1581
02:06:12,600 --> 02:06:19,995
I don't know...if
we each have a...destiny,

1582
02:06:20,080 --> 02:06:26,758
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeze...

1583
02:06:30,840 --> 02:06:35,630
But l...l think...maybe it's both.

1584
02:06:40,240 --> 02:06:43,391
Maybe both is happening
at the same time.

1585
02:06:48,840 --> 02:06:50,796
But I miss you, Jenny.

1586
02:06:56,880 --> 02:07:01,396
If there's anything you need...
I won't be far away.

1587
02:07:24,520 --> 02:07:26,397
(Birds chirping)

1588
02:07:34,880 --> 02:07:38,555
Here's your bus. OK.

1589
02:07:39,640 --> 02:07:42,473
Hey, I know this.

1590
02:07:42,560 --> 02:07:45,233
I'm gonna share that
for show-and-tell

1591
02:07:45,320 --> 02:07:47,959
because Grandma
used to read it to you.

1592
02:07:48,640 --> 02:07:50,596
My favourite book.

1593
02:07:53,400 --> 02:07:54,719
Here we are.

1594
02:07:55,760 --> 02:07:59,070
Hey. Here you go.

1595
02:08:04,240 --> 02:08:05,719
Hey, Forrest.

1596
02:08:05,800 --> 02:08:07,233
Don't...

1597
02:08:09,760 --> 02:08:12,320
I wanted to tell you I love you.

1598
02:08:12,400 --> 02:08:14,277
I love you, too, Daddy.

1599
02:08:14,360 --> 02:08:18,114
I'll be right here when you get back.

1600
02:08:18,200 --> 02:08:19,474
(Pop)

1601
02:08:22,800 --> 02:08:25,997
You understand this is
the bus to school, now, don't you?

1602
02:08:26,080 --> 02:08:30,710
Of course, and you're Dorothy Harris,
